						               													<description>Quick Panzer is the Small War rules set for World War II.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Infantry weapons, artillery mortars, antitank guns and over 100 different models of armored vehicles are all covered.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The actual rules are 2 pages long but the rules come with several annexes for those who want a lot of detail.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Two Page Rules series features rules that are 2 pages long with one combat card that has the information needed to play the game. The sequence of movement is decided by a dice roll and after that, the games follow the sequence of move-fire-move-fire. Casualties are decided simply and effectively. Morale is divided into 4 stages with the chance to rally at each stage. New players should be able to conduct their own transactions by the third move. These are combat rules that reflect the tactics and technologies of their era. Decisions are made by players, not cards or dice. These rules can be used for nearly any scale of the figure. They are great for large or small battles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
